00:42:57.626 --> 00:43:00.563
why do I feel I have the right to be in that spot

1019
00:43:00.563 --> 00:43:03.299
or I have the right to move faster than anybody else

1020
00:43:03.299 --> 00:43:04.834
who's in line right ahead of me?

1021
00:43:04.834 --> 00:43:06.068
You know and that kind of thought.

1022
00:43:06.068 --> 00:43:06.802
<v ->Good for you.</v>

1023
00:43:06.802 --> 00:43:10.773
And I mean a heartfelt to be able to realize

1024
00:43:10.773 --> 00:43:14.978
your own arrogance in that dynamic of impatience,

1025
00:43:14.978 --> 00:43:17.509
but it shows up in so many other places,

1026
00:43:17.509 --> 00:43:19.115
like anger,

1027
00:43:20.455 --> 00:43:23.385
the need of control, and that one's obvious,

1028
00:43:23.385 --> 00:43:25.254
but impatience is an absolute beauty

1029
00:43:25.254 --> 00:43:26.822
for you to pick that out of that.

1030
00:43:26.822 --> 00:43:29.725
<v Regina>Well, I find myself becoming impatient</v>

