00:43:51.513 --> 00:43:53.783
and then inevitably I'll stop myself and say,

1039
00:43:53.783 --> 00:43:56.152
"Get off it, apologize now."

1040
00:43:56.152 --> 00:43:58.521
You know, they're just living their life at their pace.

1041
00:43:58.521 --> 00:44:01.758
And so, yeah, I have a lot of apologizing going on

1042
00:44:01.758 --> 00:44:04.760
in my head when I'm out there acting impatiently

1043
00:44:04.760 --> 00:44:06.095
in the world, no doubt.

1044
00:44:06.095 --> 00:44:08.764
<v ->My lovely bride can tell you that when I'm driving a car</v>

1045
00:44:08.764 --> 00:44:12.778
it's, I get more go lights than I do stop lights.

1046
00:44:12.778 --> 00:44:14.937
<v Regina>Mm-hmm, because you're patient.</v>

1047
00:44:14.937 --> 00:44:16.639
<v ->Yeah, and I'm just not in a hurry.</v>

1048
00:44:16.639 --> 00:44:18.107
<v Regina>And I notice that, too when I--</v>

1049
00:44:18.107 --> 00:44:20.142
<v ->It doesn't mean that I don't drive very fast.</v>

1050
00:44:20.142 --> 00:44:21.510
<v Regina>Yeah, that's different,</v>

1051
00:44:21.510 --> 00:44:22.778
that's a whole separate subject.

1052
00:44:22.778 --> 00:44:24.046
<v ->No, it's just</v>

1053
00:44:24.046 --> 00:44:25.481
there's no such thing,

1054
00:44:25.481 --> 00:44:27.182
I just don't see them.

1055
00:44:28.562 --> 00:44:32.054
And, again, that's karma in motion.

1056
00:44:32.054 --> 00:44:35.458
<v Regina>Actually that's a very good point you bring up.</v>

1057
00:44:35.458 --> 00:44:37.359
Every now and then there'll be something going on

1058
00:44:37.359 --> 00:44:38.694
where it's I need to take care

1059
00:44:38.694 --> 00:44:40.329
of that thing while I'm driving.

1060
00:44:40.329 --> 00:44:41.763
Of course, I'm not gonna pull over.

1061
00:44:41.763 --> 00:44:44.734
Whatever it is, maybe I have to dial a number,

1062
00:44:44.734 --> 00:44:47.135
which is you can't do that in the state of California,

1063
00:44:47.135 --> 00:44:48.671
it's illegal so your phone.

1064
00:44:48.671 --> 00:44:50.162
Now you have to hide what you're doing.

1065
00:44:50.162 --> 00:44:52.175
Before I'd just put it up above the dash,

1066
00:44:52.175 --> 00:44:54.224
and dial so I could still see what's going on.

1067
00:44:54.224 --> 00:44:55.477
It's much more dangerous now,

1068
00:44:55.477 --> 00:44:57.345
because I'll sneak a phone call in,

1069
00:44:57.345 --> 00:45:01.784
and try to dial something down below eye-level

1070
00:45:01.784 --> 00:45:03.852
of the roads, and I know that it's stupid,

1071
00:45:03.852 --> 00:45:06.354
but that it's impatient,

1072
00:45:06.354 --> 00:45:09.759
but when I need for those red lights to happen,

1073
00:45:09.759 --> 00:45:11.413
so I can just stop and do it,

1074
00:45:11.413 --> 00:45:12.578
it will not happen.

1075
00:45:12.578 --> 00:45:13.788
<v ->Of course not.</v>

1076
00:45:13.788 --> 00:45:16.197
<v Regina>It never ceases to amaze me,</v>

1077
00:45:16.197 --> 00:45:20.403
it's all green when I need to do this impatient thing now.

1078
00:45:20.403 --> 00:45:22.003
<v ->But the root behind that is the fact</v>

1079
00:45:22.003 --> 00:45:23.639
that you already know subconsciously

1080
00:45:23.639 --> 00:45:27.977
that you are doing something that is inappropriate.

1081
00:45:27.977 --> 00:45:28.677
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

1082
00:45:28.677 --> 00:45:30.012
<v ->So the light is gonna make sure</v>

1083
00:45:30.012 --> 00:45:32.781
that you have inappropriate time to do it,

1084
00:45:32.781 --> 00:45:35.317
because that's exactly what it's giving you.

1085
00:45:35.317 --> 00:45:36.952
<v Regina>I always marvel at the beauty of that</v>

1086
00:45:36.952 --> 00:45:38.553
and how it plays out.

1087
00:45:38.553 --> 00:45:40.789
<v ->See to me, there's only harmony,</v>

1088
00:45:40.789 --> 00:45:43.659
and the idea of karma shows it to you.

1089
00:45:43.659 --> 00:45:45.160
And the question is whether you choose

1090
00:45:45.160 --> 00:45:48.799
to accept it, because there is only harmony

1091
00:45:48.799 --> 00:45:53.502
until a disharmonious human enters in,

1092
00:45:53.502 --> 00:45:55.871
and there's just a natural rhythm to life.

1093
00:45:55.871 --> 00:45:58.206
So it already knows you're attempting to do something

1094
00:45:58.206 --> 00:45:59.941
that's inappropriate, so it's gonna make sure

1095
00:45:59.941 --> 00:46:01.744
that you have inappropriate time

1096
00:46:01.744 --> 00:46:03.245
to do an inappropriate thing.

1097
00:46:03.245 --> 00:46:04.747
<v Regina>It works every time.</v>

1098
00:46:04.747 --> 00:46:05.949
<v ->Absolutely it will.</v>

1099
00:46:05.949 --> 00:46:08.150
I don't care what it is and what it's on,

1100
00:46:08.150 --> 00:46:10.486
it's always gonna give you the same thing back to you.

1101
00:46:10.486 --> 00:46:12.455
<v Regina>I love the return on it.</v>

1102
00:46:12.455 --> 00:46:14.857
Okay, let's talk about the eighth law of karma,

1103
00:46:14.857 --> 00:46:17.627
the principle of willingness.

1104
00:46:17.627 --> 00:46:19.428
That's an interesting one.

1105
00:46:19.428 --> 00:46:20.915
<v ->Um,</v>

1106
00:46:20.915 --> 00:46:22.765
let's just say that it revolves

1107
00:46:22.765 --> 00:46:26.017
more about no complaints.

1108
00:46:27.836 --> 00:46:31.858
It's just simply about willing to be who you are...

1109
00:46:32.808 --> 00:46:34.477
at all moments.
<v Regina>Authentically.</v>

1110
00:46:35.527 --> 00:46:37.013
Well, that's the only way you can be, I guess,

1111
00:46:37.013 --> 00:46:39.048
is you are or you aren't you.

1112
00:46:39.048 --> 00:46:40.882
<v ->No, you are you no matter</v>

1113
00:46:40.882 --> 00:46:43.319
what you think you are at that moment.

1114
00:46:43.319 --> 00:46:47.590
It's, the law of willingness is establishing

1115
00:46:47.590 --> 00:46:50.459
and realizing the harmony and recognizing the harmony

1116
00:46:50.459 --> 00:46:53.128
even within your own self about who you are,

1117
00:46:53.128 --> 00:46:56.245
and what you yourself are all about.

1118
00:46:56.245 --> 00:46:58.400
Love the way Bruce Lee said it.

1119
00:46:58.400 --> 00:47:00.235
Water, if you put water in a cup

1120
00:47:00.235 --> 00:47:01.605
it takes the shape of the cup.

1121
00:47:01.605 --> 00:47:02.838
If you put water in a glass,

1122
00:47:02.838 --> 00:47:04.172
it takes the shape of glass,

1123
00:47:04.172 --> 00:47:05.274
and, of course, you put it in a bowl,

1124
00:47:05.274 --> 00:47:06.409
your puppies will appreciate it,

1125
00:47:06.409 --> 00:47:08.811
because it takes the shape of the bowl.

1126
00:47:08.811 --> 00:47:10.045
We are the same way.

1127
00:47:10.045 --> 00:47:13.711
But what we do is we end up being unwilling,

1128
00:47:13.711 --> 00:47:17.219
let's say, to be a loving, kind person,

1129
00:47:17.219 --> 00:47:19.956
or even being patient in that moment.

1130
00:47:19.956 --> 00:47:23.559
It's just, goes back to the notion of acceptance.

1131
00:47:23.559 --> 00:47:26.862
And the idea of the law of willingness is just we're willing

1132
00:47:26.862 --> 00:47:28.730
to go with whatever is there.

1133
00:47:28.730 --> 00:47:31.533
And now we're back to the idea of the tree, again,

1134
00:47:31.533 --> 00:47:34.604
and the wind blowing, because the truth is

1135
00:47:34.604 --> 00:47:38.874
the way we change our outer world

1136
00:47:38.874 --> 00:47:41.710
is through our inner self.

1137
00:47:41.710 --> 00:47:44.981
And that's where the real power of the human lies.

1138
00:47:44.981 --> 00:47:48.584
And we have to actually be willing to work with that,

1139
00:47:48.584 --> 00:47:50.632
so that we can accomplish that.

1140
00:47:50.632 --> 00:47:52.655
<v Regina>One of the subtexts in that particular one</v>

1141
00:47:52.655 --> 00:47:55.257
talks about, you talked about truth a moment ago,

1142
00:47:55.257 --> 00:47:57.593
personal truth versus universal truth.

1143
00:47:57.593 --> 00:47:58.977
<v ->Hmm.</v>

1144
00:47:59.661 --> 00:48:00.529
When somebody says,

1145
00:48:00.529 --> 00:48:03.666
"Now, let me tell you my personal truth,"

1146
00:48:03.666 --> 00:48:06.501
you're about to hear an ego barking,

1147
00:48:06.501 --> 00:48:07.802
because what they're gonna tell you

1148
00:48:07.802 --> 00:48:08.937
is what they've limited

1149
00:48:08.937 --> 00:48:11.606
an otherwise universal principle to,

1150
00:48:11.606 --> 00:48:13.809
to their scope of understanding.

1151
00:48:15.589 --> 00:48:17.745
If I were to look at you and ask you a ludicrous question

1152
00:48:17.745 --> 00:48:20.648
like, where's the center of infinity?

1153
00:48:20.648 --> 00:48:21.450
What would you say?

1154
00:48:21.450 --> 00:48:22.951
<v Regina>I'd have a blank screen.</v>

1155
00:48:22.951 --> 00:48:24.319
<v ->Exactly.</v>

1156
00:48:24.319 --> 00:48:27.623
So why is science looking for the center of infinity,

1157
00:48:27.623 --> 00:48:30.192
when they already know right off the bat that doesn't exist?

1158
00:48:30.192 --> 00:48:30.993
What's my point?

1159
00:48:30.993 --> 00:48:32.262
That's a universal truth.

1160
00:48:32.262 --> 00:48:35.030
A universal truth is very obvious in itself,

1161
00:48:35.030 --> 00:48:39.741
but what people will do, is they will take a universal truth

1162
00:48:39.741 --> 00:48:43.022
which, by the way, is a way to tell them, is...

1163
00:48:44.639 --> 00:48:47.576
that that universal truth will fit anywhere.

1164
00:48:47.576 --> 00:48:48.811
It has to.

1165
00:48:48.811 --> 00:48:50.745
But a personal truth won't.

1166
00:48:50.745 --> 00:48:51.896
In fact...

1167
00:48:53.215 --> 00:48:56.819
the way the principle actually reads is to this effect:

1168
00:48:56.819 --> 00:49:00.122
That whatever you believe something to be true,

1169
00:49:00.122 --> 00:49:01.230
then you must be willing

1170
00:49:01.230 --> 00:49:03.859
to demonstrate that truth, all right?

1171
00:49:03.859 --> 00:49:07.396
Now, what do we do when we think something is true

1172
00:49:07.396 --> 00:49:10.632
and we go to demonstrate it, and it doesn't work?

1173
00:49:10.632 --> 00:49:12.334
Don't we begin to fight it?

1174
00:49:12.334 --> 00:49:13.303
<v Regina>Mm-hmm.</v>

1175
00:49:13.303 --> 00:49:15.403
<v ->So the idea of the law of willingness</v>

1176
00:49:15.403 --> 00:49:19.708
is as you grow and shift, what you deem as truth now

1177
00:49:19.708 --> 00:49:22.712
is not what you deemed as truth 10 years ago.

1178
00:49:22.712 --> 00:49:23.912
It's totally different.

1179
00:49:23.912 --> 00:49:25.814
And you've been absolutely willing

1180
00:49:25.814 --> 00:49:27.816
to shift and change with it.

1181
00:49:27.816 --> 00:49:30.652
So, if a truth doesn't work, in essence,

1182
00:49:30.652 --> 00:49:34.457
now it's time to shift your personal perspective on that.

1183
00:49:34.457 --> 00:49:36.292
But if a person is gonna look for truth,

1184
00:49:36.292 --> 00:49:38.727
look for universal truth.

1185
00:49:38.727 --> 00:49:40.562
<v Regina>Rather than the kind that says,</v>

1186
00:49:40.562 --> 00:49:42.898
"I do it this way because that's how I've always done it,

1187
00:49:42.898 --> 00:49:44.399
"that's how my family did it before me,

1188
00:49:44.399 --> 00:49:46.602
"my dad always did it that way."

1189
00:49:46.602 --> 00:49:48.030
That's what you call a personal truth.

1190
00:49:48.030 --> 00:49:49.571
<v ->Yeah, um.</v>

1191
00:49:49.571 --> 00:49:50.572
I don't know if you read

1192
00:49:50.572 --> 00:49:52.591
the story in there about the shoe,

1193
00:49:52.591 --> 00:49:54.576
when one of my teachers looked at me and said,

1194
00:49:54.576 --> 00:49:56.812
"You know, man, do you always put your right shoe on first?"

1195
00:49:56.812 --> 00:49:59.082
And I said, "Yes, I do."

1196
00:49:59.082 --> 00:50:00.059
And he said, "Why?"

1197
00:50:00.059 --> 00:50:02.485
I said, "Well, my mom taught me that.

1198
00:50:02.485 --> 00:50:04.820
"And I've been doing it that way all of my life."

1199
00:50:04.820 --> 00:50:06.322
He said, "Take your shoes off."

1200
00:50:06.322 --> 00:50:07.223
So I took them off.

1201
00:50:07.223 --> 00:50:10.125
I was getting ready to go run, so they were tennis shoes.

1202
00:50:10.125 --> 00:50:11.159
So I took them off.

1203
00:50:11.159 --> 00:50:12.861
And he said, "Now, put your left one on first,"

1204
00:50:12.861 --> 00:50:15.063
keeping in mind that I never done that,

1205
00:50:15.063 --> 00:50:17.332
and about 23, 24 years old,

1206
00:50:17.332 --> 00:50:19.267
I had never in my life had done that.

1207
00:50:19.267 --> 00:50:22.273
So I sat down on this little three-legged stool,

1208
00:50:22.273 --> 00:50:25.307
and I picked up the left shoe.

1209
00:50:25.307 --> 00:50:28.543
I went to put it on and, Regina, I fell on the floor,

1210
00:50:28.543 --> 00:50:30.513
'cause I'd never done it.

1211
00:50:30.513 --> 00:50:32.815
So, when somebody says, "My dad did it,

1212
00:50:32.815 --> 00:50:34.883
"my mom did it, my grandfather did it,

1213
00:50:34.883 --> 00:50:37.353
"so, therefore, I'm gonna do it,"

1214
00:50:37.353 --> 00:50:40.722
okay, no, you are simply repeating

1215
00:50:40.722 --> 00:50:43.225
other people's cycles and living your life

1216
00:50:43.225 --> 00:50:44.593
the way that they have.

1217
00:50:44.593 --> 00:50:45.861
<v Regina>And you bring a really good point up,</v>

1218
00:50:45.861 --> 00:50:47.930
because to start breaking these cycles,

1219
00:50:47.930 --> 00:50:50.232
it can be something as simple as recognizing

1220
00:50:50.232 --> 00:50:52.535
an ingrained pattern like you say,

1221
00:50:52.535 --> 00:50:54.470
putting the other shoe on first.

1222
00:50:54.470 --> 00:50:56.139
<v ->And more will go on up here,</v>

1223
00:50:56.139 --> 00:50:57.773
than they ever do out there.

1224
00:50:57.773 --> 00:51:01.643
But if we begin working with our own mind

1225
00:51:01.643 --> 00:51:03.746
as an example, say, you're in a situation

1226
00:51:03.746 --> 00:51:05.847
where you usually become impatient,

1227
00:51:05.847 --> 00:51:07.616
okay, it's fine, become impatient,

1228
00:51:07.616 --> 00:51:09.251
catch it, recognize it, realize it.

1229
00:51:09.251 --> 00:51:11.486
Next time that same situation comes up,

1230
00:51:11.486 --> 00:51:13.388
if you keep working at it, there's gonna come a point

1231
00:51:13.388 --> 00:51:15.191
where you're gonna find yourself in a situation

1232
00:51:15.191 --> 00:51:18.126
where you ordinarily become impatient,

1233
00:51:18.126 --> 00:51:19.361
well now you're not.

1234
00:51:19.361 --> 00:51:20.295
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

1235
00:51:20.295 --> 00:51:21.263
<v ->That's the progression.</v>

1236
00:51:21.263 --> 00:51:22.298
That's how it works.

1237
00:51:22.298 --> 00:51:25.700
And the law of willingness is also, you could say,

1238
00:51:25.700 --> 00:51:29.270
is working with your own routines of mind.

1239
00:51:29.270 --> 00:51:31.140
I love to share with people that the only habits

1240
00:51:31.140 --> 00:51:32.608
in this world nuns wear.

1241
00:51:32.608 --> 00:51:34.376
If you're not a nun, then you don't belong in a habit.

1242
00:51:34.376 --> 00:51:35.544
<v Regina>Then you don't need any.</v>

1243
00:51:35.544 --> 00:51:36.713
<v ->Exactly.</v>

1244
00:51:36.713 --> 00:51:38.375
<v Regina>What about the 10th law of karma,</v>

1245
00:51:38.375 --> 00:51:39.414
the principle of change.

1246
00:51:39.414 --> 00:51:41.386
This one scares a lot of people.

1247
00:51:42.736 --> 00:51:43.885
<v ->It actually reads this way.</v>

1248
00:51:43.885 --> 00:51:44.797
And I can remember the day

1249
00:51:44.797 --> 00:51:46.939
that Khi Ellis threw it at me.

1250
00:51:50.358 --> 00:51:51.527
(speaks foreign language)

1251
00:51:51.527 --> 00:51:53.312
How did he actually put it?

1252
00:51:53.628 --> 00:51:55.096
The more things change,

1253
00:51:55.096 --> 00:51:58.384
the more they seem to stay the same.

1254
00:52:01.337 --> 00:52:03.739
And I looked really puzzled,

1255
00:52:03.739 --> 00:52:07.226
If things change, how can they remain the same?

1256
00:52:08.143 --> 00:52:09.511
And then he began to instruct me

1257
00:52:09.511 --> 00:52:11.547
on all the wrestling matches that we do,

1258
00:52:11.547 --> 00:52:13.215
it's like a little analogy I gave you

1259
00:52:13.215 --> 00:52:15.751
with the idea of the shoe.

1260
00:52:15.751 --> 00:52:17.185
They put me in a scenario

1261
00:52:17.185 --> 00:52:20.889
that things they knew had to change.

1262
00:52:20.889 --> 00:52:24.626
And in my routines and my own mind had to change,

1263
00:52:24.626 --> 00:52:27.796
because you see, if you attempt to change

1264
00:52:27.796 --> 00:52:32.233
everything outside you, they stay the same,

